Bootstrap is a popular open-source front-end framework used to build responsive, mobile-first websites quickly and easily.

‚≠ê Key Features of Bootstrap

Pre-built CSS components
Buttons, cards, navbars, forms, tables, grids, alerts, badges, etc.

Responsive Grid System
Lets you create layouts that automatically adjust for mobile, tablet, and desktop.

Utility Classes
Hundreds of small ready-to-use classes for spacing, colors, display, flexbox, etc.

JavaScript Plugins
Includes ready scripts for modals, sliders (carousel), dropdowns, tooltips, accordions, etc.

Easy Customization
You can override default styles or use Bootstraps custom themes.

 Why Developers Use Bootstrap

Saves time in coding UI from scratch

Ensures responsive design automatically

Works well with every browser

Large community + great documentation
